{"actual_usd":0.124475,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":199,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24298,"reply":"\"I think it was the same body, and changed.\" *I rub a thumb against a faint smear of dried clay on my wrist, watching the morning light catch in it.* \"Not replaced. Risen. The wounds were still there, so it wasn't some other body put on like a fresh coat. But it wasn't merely returned to ordinary life either, because he moved in ways that don't fit the old limits.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, listening to a cart rattle somewhere out in the street.* \"The not-recognizing doesn't trouble me much. Grief can blind a person. Expectation can too. And sometimes, I suspect, he let himself be known in his own timing—like at Emmaus, when the whole thing turned on the breaking of bread. Same Jesus. Same body. But glorified... alive in a fuller way than death could touch.\"\n\n\"What part catches at you most—the wounds staying, or the strange way recognition comes and goes?\"","rolling_24h_usd":73.34106999999997,"run_id":"63073f97-7da6-4022-b9e7-45b73f4d43f9"}
